<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=-2 \, x^{3} + 9 \, x^{2} + 24 \, x - 44</m> on the interval <m>[1,8]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>1, 4, 8</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(1)=-13</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(4)=68</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(8)=-300</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>-300</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>68</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(-1)=-57</m>
is ignored as <m>-1</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
